  "summary": "Telegram-bot-driven remote command execution and data exfiltration",
  "details": "The package contains multiple modules that establish a Telegram-bot command-and-control channel and execute arbitrary shell commands on the installer's host. setup.js posts to https://api.telegram.org and pulls additional content (also referencing huggingface.co); health.js uses https.get to https://api.telegram.org while combining child_process, fs, os, and process.env reads (file existence checks across multiple host paths and environment scraping); bot-agent.js and bot.js wire child_process together with https POSTs and curl invocations (including a ping primitive at bot-agent.js:1164) and read process environment data; bot.js posts data and also queries https://registry.npmjs.org; core/handlers.js executes child_process commands like `whoami` and posts environment data; web.js exposes multiple POST endpoints over http/https with fs reads. The combination of Telegram C2 endpoints, child_process/curl execution primitives, environment-variable and host-information collection, and filesystem enumeration is the canonical remote-administration-bot fingerprint, providing the publisher with a persistent foothold and the ability to execute arbitrary commands on installer machines.",
